The paper proposes a method for generating feasible 6-DoF grasp poses for unknown objects in unrestricted workspace with reachability awareness. This involves the use of a voxel-based deep 3D CNN and simulation to train the network on a large-scale synthetic dataset. The problem of grasping objects is a common one in robotics, and the use of deep learning techniques to address it falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper involves the use of computer vision techniques to process the 3D voxel data, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques to generate grasp poses also falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of simulation to train the network, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
